50|$|Tin Moe {{was born}} Maung Ba Gyan {{in the village}} of Kanmyè in Taungtha Township, Myingyan, Mandalay Division. He {{received}} his early education at a Buddhist monastery, and attended school at the town of <b>Yezagyo.</b> His reputation preceded him when he went on to study at the University of Mandalay at the request of faculty members who had been impressed by an essay he wrote for the matriculation exam. He was already a published poet under the pen name Kan Myè Nan Myint Nwe in the Ludu Journal of Mandalay.|$|E

